<HEADER>
A5965 &Cx1f; tad-z
r k &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-COMMENTARY-BJT29-COX     07-28 0500
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-COMMENTARY-BJT29-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE WEDNESDAY COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Wednesday, July 29, 1998, are moving
today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ African Americans have fought to win, save and
expand American freedom in every of the nation's wars, only to be
rewarded after each, if rewarded at all, with meager rations from
that freedom _ and with quick white forgetfulness. We were still
rescuing those memories last week, and settling those debts.
(Teepen, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ Miami may be muggy but it's not much
different than arid Sacramento when it comes to uncomfortable
weather: hot is hot, no matter how wet or dry it is. Howard
Kleinberg is a former editor of the Miami News. (Kleinberg, Cox
News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   KABAT-COLUMN _ It pains me to say this, but we have a clumsy
dog. From the very first, Sandy was, shall we say, uncoordinated.
She would sit, and her back legs would splay out haphazardly, her
rear skittering across the floor. Sitting, much less sitting up,
seemed to be well beyond her ability. We always felt like we needed
to prop up her backside when she tried to sit. ``What's wrong with
her back legs?'' we asked a friend who knows a thing or two about
dogs. ``Are they weak?'' ``Nope. She's just clumsy,'' we were told.
(Kabat, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MSKUBE-COLUMN _ We are a listing nation. Not in the maritime
sense of a ship taking on water, but in our mania for ranking
things. Usually by 10s. We rank the 10 Best Steakhouses, 10 Best
Beaches No One Knows About (after which, everyone does), 10 Best
Mutual Funds ... The Associated Press started all this when it
began ranking the Top 10 college football teams. (Skube, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED 7/27.
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ It must be a joke. Congressman John Kasich poses
before the National Debt Clock on the ``Kasich 2000'' web page that
touts him as presidential material. The numbers on that clock _
$5.36 trillion as of Monday, $20,490 per person _ are supposed to
alarm us all to action. What kind of action? Gut-wrenching
patriotic sacrifice? Visionary tough decisions? You must be joking.
(Young, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio. Feminism was not a word in my
Grandmother Parker's vocabulary. She lived and died too soon, long
before Betty and Gloria showed up and much too long before I was of
an age where we might have talked woman-to-woman. And that is too
bad. Mrs. Parker (I was encouraged to call her that to avoid what
she referred to as ``simpering sobriquet'') was, without doubt, a
woman ahead of her time. (Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
