to prop up her backside when she tried to sit. ``What's wrong with
her back legs?'' we asked a friend who knows a thing or two about
dogs. ``Are they weak?'' ``Nope. She's just clumsy,'' we were told.
(Kabat, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MSKUBE-COLUMN _ We are a listing nation. Not in the maritime
sense of a ship taking on water, but in our mania for ranking
things. Usually by 10s. We rank the 10 Best Steakhouses, 10 Best
Beaches No One Knows About (after which, everyone does), 10 Best
Mutual Funds ... The Associated Press started all this when it
began ranking the Top 10 college football teams. (Skube, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED 7/27.
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ It must be a joke. Congressman John Kasich poses
before the National Debt Clock on the ``Kasich 2000'' web page that
touts him as presidential material. The numbers on that clock _
$5.36 trillion as of Monday, $20,490 per person _ are supposed to
alarm us all to action. What kind of action? Gut-wrenching
patriotic sacrifice? Visionary tough decisions? You must be joking.
(Young, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio. Feminism was not a word in my
Grandmother Parker's vocabulary. She lived and died too soon, long
before Betty and Gloria showed up and much too long before I was of
an age where we might have talked woman-to-woman. And that is too
bad. Mrs. Parker (I was encouraged to call her that to avoid what
she referred to as ``simpering sobriquet'') was, without doubt, a
woman ahead of her time. (Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
