<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Wednesday, July 29, and thereafter. If you have any questions,
please call Tina May at (206) 448-8355.
</P>
<P>
   AUTHOR-KINDER (Undated) Seattle author Gary Kinder devoted a
decade of his life to writing ``Ship of Gold in the Deep Blue
Sea,'' the story of the 1857 sinking of a ship carrying gold from
California off the Carolina coast in which more than 400 people
died and of its discovery in the 1980s. Kinder talks about personal
costs and the problems in getting the best-seller into print. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   By John Marshall. (story will move in the ``e '' category)
</P>
<P>
   LIVING-COLUMN-HAHN (Undated) There are no fireflies in Seattle
because they get turned on and burn out too fast.
</P>
<P>
   By Jon Hahn. (story will move in the ``l'' category)
</P>
