<HEADLINE>
SNORKEL BOB SHOWS THE WAY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By RICHARD P. CARPENTER  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Strange but true: These are actual titles of travel guides,
provided by the Travel Books and Language Center.
</P>
<P>
   _``Snorkel Bob's Reality (&AMP; Getdown) Guide to Hawaii.''
</P>
<P>
   _``Bed &AMP; Breakfast Lithuania.''
</P>
<P>
   _``Cockroach Hall of Fame and 101 Other Off-the-Wall Museums.''
(We actually own that one and find it a valuable resource in
seeking out our Museum of the Month.)
</P>
<P>
   _``Australian Bare Facts: Guide to Australia's Nude and Dress
Optional Clubs, Resorts, and Beaches''
</P>
<P>
   _``Why Greenland Is an Island, Australia Is Not, and Japan Is Up
for Grabs.''
</P>
<P>
   _``Music in Every Room: Around the World in a Bad Mood.''
</P>
<P>
   _``Central America by Chickenbus.''
</P>
<P>
   _``Willy Whitefeather's Outdoor Survival Handbook for Kids.''
</P>
<P>
   _``Volleyball with the Cuna Indians and Other Gay Travel
Adventures.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
---- &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; Travel Trivia: &LR;  In what Egyptian city will you find Cheops's
Pyramid? (Answer at end of column.)
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
---- &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; In a name: &LR;  How times have changed. In the 1870s, Pittsburgh's
nickname was the Gateway to the West.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
---- &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; Quotable: &LR;  ``He who would bring home the wealth of the Indies must
carry the wealth of the Indies with him.'' _ Spanish proverb.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
---- &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; Men, men everywhere ...: &LR;  Single women are expected to converge on
the Sheraton Anchorage Hotel in Alaska the weekend of Sept. 11-12
for the fifth annual National Singles Convention. Says the keynote
speaker, Roich Gosse: ``The smart women look where there is a
surplus of men _ which happens to be Alaska.'' (For more
information on the convention, call 415-459-3817.)
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
---- &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; ... Well, maybe not:  &LR; Alaska's reputation as a dating paradise for
women is, alas, greatly exaggerated, Reuters news service reports.
State figures show that the population is almost evenly divided,
with 109 males to every 100 females. What's more, there's the
situation alluded to on some T-shirts: ``Alaska Men: The odds are
good, but the goods are odd.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
---- &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; It's contest time: &LR;  For a chance to win a weeklong luxury vacation
to Paris, with round-trip flights on the Concorde, visit
www.expedia.com or write to Expedia.com/ &QC; 
Air France ``City of Light'' Sweepstakes, PO Box 5176, El Toro, CA
92630. The contest ends Aug. 15.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
---- &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; Who knew?  &LR; There is a Leaning Tower of Pisa in Niles, Ill., on the
grounds of the YMCA. The half-size replica was built to house a
water tower, and while all details aren't exact, its proportions
and detailing were painstakingly duplicated from the orginal in
Italy. Guess what the sister city of Niles, Ill., is? Right: Pisa,
Italy. (With thanks to Mrs. T. Evans of Hingham.)
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
