<P>
   PRIVACY _ WASHINGTON _ Many Americans are misled with the
thought that their medical records are safe from prying eyes,
according to a new study released Tuesday by a non-profit group. In
``Nothing Sacred: The Politics of Policy,'' the Center for Public
Integrity claims that health care records are available to anyone,
often without the knowledge or permission of patients. (Shook, Cox
News Service)
</P>
<P>
   SHOOTINGS-MEMORIAL _ WASHINGTON _ President Clinton will join
members of Congress Tuesday at a memorial service for the two
Capitol Hill police officers slain last Friday when a gunman
stormed the Capitol in a blaze of gunfire. (Harlan, Cox News
Service). WITH PHOTOS.
