</P>
<P>
   With
</P>
<P>
   GTE-DEAL (Undated) _ Examining the terms of the deal. By
Gretchen Morgenson.
</P>
<P>
   GM-STRIKE (Flint, Mich.) _ Developments in th GM strike as both
sides say they are close to an accord. By Keith Bradsher.
</P>
<P>
   CENDANT (Undated) _ Cendant says the accounting firm auditing
its financial records concurs with a previous estimate that 1997
earnings will have to be adjusted between 22 cents and 28 cents a
share. By Kenneth N. Gilpin.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-ANTITRUST (Undated) _ Microsoft files its latest
response to the Justice Department. By Steve Lohr.
</P>
<P>
   ROLLS-ROYCE (London) _ Volkswagen agrees with BMW to divide
Rolls-Royce Motor Cars, which will be split into Bentley Motor
Cars, controlled by Volkswagen, and Rolls-Royce Motor Cars, owned
by BMW. Vickers agreed earlier this month to sell Rolls-Royce to
Volkswagen; although the German company had signed the contract, it
had not reached an agreement for use of the brand name with the
brand's owner, Rolls-Royce PLC. By Alan Cowell.
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS-TRAVEL (Undated) _ The weekly Business Travel column.
By Edwin McDowell.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-EXIM (Hong Kong) _ The United States Export-Import Bank is
emphasizing China lending. By Mark Landler.
</P>
<P>
   MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ The daily Market Place column.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ Stock market developments: The Dow Jones
Industrial Average was down 162 points at midday. By Sharon R.
King.
</P>
