 Attn Sports Editors:  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Sports stories in sight at this hour from The New York Times
News Service for  &UR; WEDNESDAY &LR; , July 29.
</P>
<P>
   For information and repeats call the News Service at (212)
556-1927. And be sure to look for other sports stories from our
partners: Bloomberg News, The Boston Globe, Cox News Service,
Hearst News Service, The Houston Chronicle, The Arizona Republic,
Kansas City Star, Fort Worth Star-Telegram, Los Angeles Daily News,
San Francisco Chronicle and Seattle Post-Intelligencer.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-ANDERSON-COLUMN (Albany, N.Y.) _ Sports of The Times column
on Ernie Accorsi, the new General Manager of the Giants. By Dave
Anderson.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-GIANTS (Albany, N.Y.) _ Giants camp feature. By Bill
Pennington.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-JETS (Hempstead, N.Y.) _ If it wasn't clear before that Bill
Parcells was rooting for Glenn Foley to succeed, it was evident
today as the Jets coach made excuses for the young quarterback,
gave him the benefit of the doubt and basically paved a path for
him to succeed.
</P>
<P>
   Other pro football as needed.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-YANKS-ANGELS (Anaheim, Calif.) _ Yankees at Anaheim, 10:05
p.m. ET start. By Buster Olney.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-METS-PADRES New York) _ San Diego at the Mets, 7:40 p.m. ET
start. By Jack Curry.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MOST-VALUABLE (St. Louis) _ McGwire or Sosa? Suppose McGwire
finishes with 63 homers _ the number being projected, Griffey with
61 and Sosa with 59. But say Chicago makes the playoffs while St.
Louis and Seattle go packing. Who is more valuable? By William C.
Rhoden.
</P>
<P>
   SWIM-GOODWILL (Uniondale, N.Y.) _ Goodwill Games swimming: Jenny
Thompson, world champion in 100 free and 100 butterfly. By Frank
Litsky.
</P>
<P>
   BOX-GOODWILL (New York) _ Goodwill Games boxing: In U.S.-Cuban
rivalry, U.S. scores two upsets.
</P>
<P>
   SKATE-GOODWILL (Uniondale, N.Y.) _ Michele Kwan holds news
conference in advance of figure skating competition. By Jere
Longman.
