</P>
<P>
   TOUR-DE-FRANCE-DRUGS (Albertville, France) _ The Tour de France
drug problem widens as a third team is caught with illegal drugs
and police apparently raid the hotel room of a Dutch team. By
Samuel Abt.
</P>
<P>
   TOUR-DE-FRANCE (Albertville) _ Jan Ullrich, a German who leads
the Telekom team, moved up from fourth place over all to third and
almost to second, but did not go far toward winning the race for
the second successive year. That was left to Marco Pantani, who
finished second in a sprint finish and widened his lead to 5:42
over American Bobby Julich in second place and 5:56 over Ullrich.
By Samuel Abt.
</P>
