 &HT;    INFORMATION IF YOU GO TO THE MCCARTNEY HOUSE
 &HT;    With MCCARTNEY-HOUSE-0729.
 &HT;    Moving in both the (i) International and (l) Lifestyle
categories.
 &HT;    By BERT ROUGHTON JR. 
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   WHAT: Paul McCartney's teenage home
</P>
<P>
   WHERE: Liverpool, England
</P>
<P>
   HOW TO GET THERE: Fly in to either Manchester or London and buy
a ticket to ride on the train.
</P>
<P>
   TICKETS: From the U.S., call 011-44-151-486-4006, Tuesday
through Sunday between 4:30 a.m. and 12:30 P.M. (EDT). A daily
limit of six parties of 14 will be allowed.
</P>
<P>
   PRICES: Adults, $7.50; children, $4.15
</P>
<P>
   WHEN OPEN: July 29 to Oct. 31, Wednesday, Thursday and Saturday,
noon to 5 p.m.; Nov. 7 to Dec. 12; Saturdays only, noon to 4 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   DETAILS: A minibus picks up visitors at nearby Speke Hall and
delivers them at the end of Forthlin Road, a short walk from the
McCartney house. There is no automobile access. Handicapped access
is limited and the tour is restricted to the first floor only.
</P>
