<SLUG> BC-WINE-TASTINGS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WINE TASTINGS: A BIT OF SUGAR 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Texas)   (bl)  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Llano Estacado Chenin Blanc 1997, Lubbock, Texas. About $8.
</P>
<P>
   The people at Llano believe that chenin blanc is a vinifera
variety that is particularly well suited to Texas. Tasting this
wine leads me to believe that they are on the right track.
</P>
<P>
   The fruit is up front in this interpretation, and there is a
smidgen of residual sugar to please newcomers to wine drinking. I
could do without it, but then I've been drinking chenin blanc for a
long time.
</P>
<P>
   The Texans recommend this chenin blanc as a partner for
Southwestern food. Probably so, but it will be tough to convert the
hard-core beer fans. I think it makes a nice aperitif.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
