   WOLE _ Nobel laureate Wole Soyinka fled his native Nigeria in
1994 to escape imprisonment. Now, though it is certainly no prison,
he feels confined to the United States, unable to leave for fear he
will not be allowed to re-enter the country. (Melvin, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
