that was granted Tuesday to Monica Lewinsky and her mother means
they will not be prosecuted for any testimony they may give in
Kenneth Starr's investigation. What is transactional immunity? How
often is it used by prosecutors? And what might it tell us about
where Starr's probe is heading? (Deans, CoxNews Service)
</P>
<P>
   w/MONICA _ Monica Lewinsky's More Tales of the Nation blasted
onto TV sets Tuesday. And, even though polls say the country's not
interested, the media speculation begins. (Jubera, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
