</P>
<P>
   CREDIBLE _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Embarrassing retractions and admitted
fabrications have caused media credibility to come under fire this
summer. In the wake of CNN's apology for an erroneous report
alleging that the U.S. military used nerve gas on defectors and
civilians during the Vietnam War, a recent Newsweek opinion poll
found that a majority of Americans believe news reports are often
inaccurate. Even more, 63 percent, say recent inaccuracies have
made them less likely to believe news reports. (Holloway, Austin
American-Statesman). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   GANG-INJUNCTION _ State district judge Wil Flowers could decide
today whether to approve Texas' first gang injunction. Testimony
from police officers is expected to conclude today in a hearing in
the case of six alleged gang members. Prosecutors are seeking to
secure a permanent injunction that would prohibit them from
gathering together in public places. (Shah, Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-WATER _ AUSTIN, Texas _A parched Austin is 5.63 inches
below normal rainfall for the year. After recording only 1.56
inches of rain in June, Austin has seen just .9 inches this month.
In response to the drought, Motorola has been using rainwater
collected in its retention pond to water the grass and turning up
office thermostats to use less water in cooling towers that power
the air conditioning. Other big users are trying somewhat similar
methods to conserve. (Daniel, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   DELTA-NOPETS _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Delta is grounding pets
from travelling in the luggage compartments of its planes until
mid-September. Airline says it's too hot. What took so long? And
what are other airlines doing? (10-12 inches) (Hayes, Palm Beach
Post)
</P>
<P>
   SMUGGLER-ARRESTED _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Ex-mortgage broker
William Pace, a felon for defrauding banks, was arrested for
smuggling Indians into the U.S. (Pallesen, Palm Beach Post) (10-12
inches )
</P>
<P>
   FLORIDA-VOTERS (10 inches) _ TALLAHASSEE, Fla. _ The Florida
Constitution Revision Commission unveils a survey showing what
voters know about proposed revisions that will appear on the
general election ballot this fall. The commission also talks about
how to teach voters about the revisions. Only 36 percent of voters
support eliminating two cabinet posts but they like gun control and
equal rights for women by large margins on the fall ballot.
(Elmore, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   HOUSE-ARREST _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Folks wearing an
electronic house-arrest monitor will get one chance to claim the
device malfunctioned, after that, they're going back to jail. Palm
Beach County's chief judge said Tuesday that he will begin writing
new guidelines today. (Stapelton, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
