   MEXICO-ABORTION (Mexico City) -- For the first time in memory a
Mexican health minister says the nation's strict abortion laws
should be eased. By Richard Chacon. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   PROBE-LEWINSKY (Washington) -- Monica Lewinsky and her mother
are granted ``transactional'' _ or full _ immunity by independent
counsel Kenneth Starr in exchange for their testimony. By Brian
McGrory. 1400 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   PROBE-CLINTON (Washington) _ Monica Lewinsky's immunity deal
could prompt Democrats to put new pressure on President Clinton to
tell everything about the former White House intern. By Michael
Kranish and Chris Black. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   PROBE-IMMUNITY (Washington) -- ``Transactional immunity'' is a
signal Monica Lewinsky is almost certain to contradict the
president on the question of a sexual relationship between them. By
Ann Scales and Louise D. Palmer. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   CAPITOL-ROTUNDA (Washington) -- Slain police officers lie in
state in the Capitol Rotunda. President, congressional leaders
speak at memorial service. By Bob Hohler. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   THOMAS-LAWYERS (Undated) -- Justice Clarence Thomas's planned
appearance before the country's largest association of black
lawyers and judges ignites a firestorm in a long-running battle
pitting him against civil rights leaders. By Adrian Walker. 1400
words.
</P>
<P>
   POWERBALL-WARNING (Undated) -- N.H. lottery official warns
bettors not to let Wednesday's $250 million Powerball jackpot lure
them into spending more than they can afford. Odds of winning: 1 in
80.1 million. By Thomas Farragher. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   GTE-BELL (Undated) -- Insisting their combination is a ``merger
of equals,'' GTE and Bell Atlantic officials announce &UR;  &LR; a $52.8
billion stock agreement to create the nation's largest local phone
company. But GTE shareholders may question the financial terms as
not lucrative enough; others raise concerns over whether the
transaction improves competition. By Ronald Rosenberg. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BBA-REDSOX-ATHLETICS (Oakland, Calif.) _ By Gordon Edes.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PATRIOTS (Smithfield, R.I.) _ Chad Eaton is playing well
enough to be pushing both Mark Wheeler and Henry Thomas for a
starting tackle job. By Nick Cafardo.
</P>
<P>
   CYC-TOUR (Albertville, France) _ Italian Marco Pantani just
barely misses winning the race, but keeps his overall lead. By
Susan Bickelhaupt.
</P>
