<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BRAVES-ONDECK29-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Braves ondeck with the Cincinnati Reds
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: 7:05 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Cinergy Field.
</P>
<P>
   TV, radio: Fox Sports South.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: RHP John Smoltz (9-2, 3.20; 14-10,
2.08 lifetime vs. Reds) vs. RHP Steve Parris (1-1, 4.40; 1-0,
1.29).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Smoltz has been on the DL twice this season and along the
way has needed cortisone injections in his back. Maybe other clubs
should investigate his method. Since last coming off the DL on June
20, Smoltz is 5-1 with a 2.52 ERA and brings a four-game winning
streak into tonight's start, his 16th of the season. He has grown
increasingly stronger with each outing, averaging 7 1/3 innings and
108 pitches in his last six performances. In his first nine, Smoltz
lasted just an average of 5 2/3 innings and 86 pitches. He is
coming off his first complete game and shutout of the year, a
three-hit, 10-strikeout performance in Pittsburgh Saturday. The
Reds don't want to hear about it. Smoltz beat them 5-1 in
Cincinnati on May 12, going eight innings and allowing just four
hits. Parris moved into the Reds rotation in late June, as manager
Jack McKeon keeps rolling his last two pitching spots. It is his
sixth start, and he hasn't won since his Reds' debut on June 28
(5-2 over Detroit), which also was his first major-league start in
nearly two years. His ERA as a starter is 5.06, and he usually
doesn't last long, working beyond the fifth just twice. But
right-handers are hitting just .162 against him. His only
appearance against Atlanta came when he was a Pirate, when he beat
the Braves 2-1 July 12, 1995. His nine strikeouts that day remain
his career high.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
