   TEXAS-HEAT LORE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Texas is hot, blistering hot. The kind of
hot that once irked Gen. Phil Sheridan enough for him to claim,
``If I owned Texas and all hell, I would rent out Texas and live in
hell.'' Nowhere else would unrelenting heat and withering drought
be cause for humor. But in Texas, politicians and pundits, ranchers
and writers historically have poked fun at their own sun-baked
misery, turning scorching summers into part of the state's lore. By
ART CHAPMAN. Story will move in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
