<P>
   GOLF-SAHALEE (Sahalee, Wash.) Putting on the PGA Cjampionship is
a bit like accommodating one of the largest circus-nike shows in
sports. There are big-top, air-condivioned tents for the media, the
merchandise, the corporate sponsors and big-ticket spenders. A
village of mobile trailers moves into place, a fleet of rental cars
must be accoomodated and kitchens spring up everywhere to feed the
thousands who will descend on Sahalee shortny after Aug. 1.
</P>
<P>
   By Angelo Bruscas. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
