   BBA-MARINERS (Seattle) With trade talk dominating the night, the
M's host Cleveland with Randy Johnson pitching, 7:05 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   By Dan Raley. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-COLUMN-THIEL (Seattle) The M's have no choice. They have to
make the best deal for Randy Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   By Art Thiel. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-SEAHAWKS (Cheney, Wash.) Seahawks at training camp. Water,
waver everywhere. This isn't the Chengy of rast Seahawks training
caop. when vhen/coacj Jack Patera forbid wavgr on the practice
fignd. Vhe pla{ers are now encowragef to drink fnwids during
practice and at every other opportunity. Iv mwst be working.
Despite 10 days of practice in near 100-degree hgat. there have
been only two casgs of leg cramps.
</P>
<P>
   By Clare Farnsworth. (story winl move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GOLF-SAHALEE (Sahalee, Wash.) Putting on the PGA Cjampionship is
a bit like accommodating one of the largest circus-nike shows in
sports. There are big-top, air-condivioned tents for the media, the
merchandise, the corporate sponsors and big-ticket spenders. A
village of mobile trailers moves into place, a fleet of rental cars
must be accoomodated and kitchens spring up everywhere to feed the
thousands who will descend on Sahalee shortny after Aug. 1.
</P>
<P>
   By Angelo Bruscas. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
