   The Scottish Daily Record went on the record when Connery failed
to make knighthood in June, at the same time poking fun at the
suave actor's pronunciation: ``Sean is shnubbed onsh more! ... It
is another shameful rebuff for Scotland's No. 1 son, verging on a
national insult.''
</P>
<P>
   (Meanwhile, the Telegraph reports that  &UR; Queen Elizabeth  &LR; made
 &UR; Petula Clark &LR;  a CBE, Commander of the British Empire, in ceremonies
at Buckingham Palace last week.)
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Arnold Schwarzenegger &LR; , who with special permission, holds
dual citizenship in the United States and Austria, may decide to
run for the presidency of Austria. Schwarzenegger was last there
for the second (and final) inauguration of  &UR; Thomas Klestil &LR; , whose
term is six years long.
</P>
<P>
   The movie star ``has ambitions,'' Austrian diplomat  &UR; Hans &LR; 
 &UR; Janitschek &LR;  told the New York Post. ``There is no doubt about it.
And I think he has a better chance of getting elected president of
Austria than he does governor of California.''
</P>
<P>
   ``He will be the crown of our country,'' columnist  &UR; Wolf &LR; 
 &UR; Martin &LR;  of Kronenzeitung wrote. ``Let him enjoy his success in the
world in little Austria.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ Rolling Stone's What's Hot for Summer list says that the
tattoo to have right now is a vertical line extending the natural
one upon which one sits.
</P>
<P>
   _ New regulations allow importers to bring into the United
States from Canada 30 Beanie Babies every 30 days.
</P>
<P>
   _ On his private island in Tahiti, &UR; Marlon Brando &LR;  is said to be
teaching himself how to oil paint.
</P>
<P>
   _ The California Department of Food and Agriculture's
announcement of San Jose's fruit fly eradication program seems to
have taken its plot from a  &UR; Margaret Atwood &LR;  novel. The plan is for
``male annihilation.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Robert Redford &LR; , who will be in London to promote ``The Horse
Whisperer,'' said he had a scheduling conflict when he turned down
an invitation to have tea with  &UR; Queen Elizabeth &LR; , the most noble
horse whisperer of all.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; S.F. COPS PLAN TO GO BALD &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The head of Captain  &UR; Walter Cullop  &LR; of the Northern Police
Station will be shaved bald in front of City Hall on August 14, as
one step in Buzz the Fuzz, a fund-raising drive for terminally ill
kids.
</P>
<P>
   The idea _ cops get dollar sponsors for shaving their heads, &LR; 
and then give the money to charity _ originated as Crop a Cop in
Australia, where $2 million was raised last year.
</P>
<P>
   A few kick-off events have already taken place in San Francisco.
The Dean of Women at Mercy High School shaved her head a few weeks
ago, and  &UR; Stephen Weaver &LR;  of the Horseshoe Tavern in the Marina
shaved his head last week.
</P>
<P>
   The grand shaving will take place at the Sound Factory on
October 24; it will be followed by a Baldy Bash at Bimbo's.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``When you see Barbara Walters sitting at the foot of a bed with
Dennis Rodman, and naming him one of her 10 most fascinating people
of whatever year that was, you know that Barbara Walters has long
since sold out. Because Barbara Walters doesn't remotely believe
that Dennis Rodman is fascinating. What she thinks is fascinating
is an 18.6 rating instead of a 16.4 rating, and if Dennis Rodman
can help her get it, she's willing to do that. That's her version
of Jerry Springer letting people throw chairs at one another.''
</P>
<P>
   _ NBC's  &UR; Bob Costas &LR;  in the Los Angeles Times.
</P>
