<P>
   GTE-DEAL (New York) _ It isn't often that a merger announcement
drives down the prices of stocks across an industry. But it
happened on Tuesday, as investors absorbed the news that Bell
Atlantic was paying $53 billion in stock for the GTE Corp. in a
deal structured as a merger of equals. At the end of the day's
trading, the Bell Atlantic-GTE combination looked more like the pin
that burst the telecommunications stock bubble than a go-go
megamerger. The group, which had traded at a price-earnings
multiple of 27 earlier this year, was down to a below-market
multiple of 21 on Tuesday. Months of merger hype and investor hopes
went pop. Like that. By Gretchen Morgenson.
</P>
