being sent for use with BELL-GTE-BOS.)
</P>
<P>
   (Bottom)
</P>
<P>
   PRICE-MARKETPLACE (New York) _ Ever since Michael F. Price sold
the manager of the Mutual Series family of funds to the Franklin
Templeton Group for a small fortune two years ago, the funds have
labored under a cloud of uncertainty. Shareholders have waited
nervously for the day Price would give up stock-picking on his own
and fly off to his vacation home in Colorado. Price cleared the air
on Tuesday, announcing that he will step down as chief executive of
the group effective Nov. 1, taking advantage of an option outlined
in his contract which allowed him to depart on the second
anniversary of the company's sale. By Edward Wyatt.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET.)
</P>
