   MARKET (New York) _ There were twists and turns and wild
gyrations in the stock market on Tuesday, as continuing concerns
about corporate profits, Asia's financial crisis and the specter of
political upheaval in Washington pushed stocks lower. At one point,
the Dow Jones industrial average was down 212.15 points, before
bargain hunters ratcheted it upward to trim its loss to 93.46
points. By Sharon R. King.
