<HEADLINE>
DISNEY CRUISE LINE NOT FINDING SMOOTH SAILING FOR INAUGURAL VOYAGE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DAVE McNARY  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES -- Walt Disney Co.'s much-hyped cruise line, set for
launch this week, continues to navigate in rough waters.
</P>
<P>
   Travel agents have reported less-than-expected demand for summer
cruises on the Disney Magic, with rooms still available as early as
Aug. 14. The Cruise Week newsletter has reported that 72 percent of
more than 300 agents polled said they were booking few or no
customers on the ship.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's incredible there are still rooms available next month,
because a typical new ship would be sold out,'' said newsletter
publisher Michael Driscoll of Wilmington, N.C.
</P>
<P>
   He blamed Disney's newcomer status and delays in the inaugural
cruise, which added up to 4{ months, for the tepid reception.
``It's tough to sell something sight unseen,'' Driscoll said,
adding that his polling found that 88 percent of agents think
business will pick up once the first cruise is completed.
</P>
<P>
   Scott Barry, an analyst with Raymond James &AMP; Associates, agrees
that the delays -- brought on by a lack of cruise-ship construction
-- have probably dampened early interest in Disney Magic. ``Once it
starts, the word-of-mouth should be very strong even though it's
priced significantly above competitors,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   John Severini, the cruise line's vice president of sales and
passenger services, said advance bookings have topped internal
estimates. ``We are launching an incredible product, and our phones
have been ringing off the hook,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Disney's fares are about 30 percent higher than those of its
rivals, reflecting the strategy that the strong brand name and
larger-than-average rooms will carry considerable customer appeal.
The two-person rate for an outside room with a veranda on its
three-day cruise from Port Canaveral, Fla., on Aug. 14 is $2,565;
Carnival's balcony room on a three-day cruise, starting Aug. 13
from the same port aboard the Fantasy, is $1,882.
</P>
<P>
   XXX
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
